97
00:05:54,850 --> 00:05:56,850
- This is crazy.
- Pardon?

98
00:05:56,850 --> 00:05:58,090
What? Nothing.

99
00:05:59,189 --> 00:06:01,920
Can I pay this in installments?

100
00:06:02,420 --> 00:06:03,790
For how many months?

101
00:06:04,889 --> 00:06:06,790
If you get the surgery, you'll have a year.

102
00:06:06,790 --> 00:06:08,230
Without it, you'll have 3 to 4 months.

103
00:06:10,929 --> 00:06:12,770
Three months, please.

104
00:06:12,770 --> 00:06:13,770
Okay.

105
00:06:14,770 --> 00:06:17,600
- Hey, get ready for a patient!
- Please take good care of him.

106
00:06:18,009 --> 00:06:20,239
- This way.
- Keep pushing.

107
00:06:20,239 --> 00:06:21,239
Excuse us.

108
00:06:21,239 --> 00:06:22,910
- He needs a doctor now.
- This way.

109
00:06:23,179 --> 00:06:24,309
Oh, no.

110
00:06:24,610 --> 00:06:26,780
- Over here.
- Take that off.

111
00:06:26,949 --> 00:06:28,580
The stab wound in the abdomen is severe.

112
00:06:28,580 --> 00:06:30,480
- And the bleeding is serious too.
- Sir, stay with me.

113
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:32,090
- Sir.
- His BP is dropping.

114
00:06:32,090 --> 00:06:33,150
Not yet.

115
00:06:33,150 --> 00:06:35,460
- We have a patient!
- This way.

116
00:06:37,489 --> 00:06:38,530
He's here.

117
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:43,960
- All right. 1, 2, 3.
- 1, 2, 3.

118
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:49,369
He's the suspect.

119
00:06:49,369 --> 00:06:50,670
He tried to kill himself at the scene.

120
00:06:50,670 --> 00:06:52,040
And the police are on their way here.

121
00:06:58,850 --> 00:06:59,980
A patient is coming in.

122
00:07:04,249 --> 00:07:05,720
I'm sorry. Which department...

123
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:25,869
Put curtains around the patient.

124
00:07:25,869 --> 00:07:27,840
And don't let anyone pass through other than the police officers.

125
00:07:28,980 --> 00:07:30,040
Yes, doctor.

126
00:07:32,379 --> 00:07:34,080
I'll take it from here. You can leave now.

127
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:36,679
- Pardon? But he...
- He won't die.

128
00:07:38,350 --> 00:07:39,389
Okay.

129
00:07:58,610 --> 00:07:59,739
Where do you think you're going?

130
00:08:00,570 --> 00:08:01,639
Open your eyes.

131
00:08:06,649 --> 00:08:07,879
I've been waiting. Why took you so long?

132
00:08:07,879 --> 00:08:09,119
You think you're the man of the hour?

133
00:08:10,649 --> 00:08:12,249
You must feel like you're in control.

134
00:08:12,519 --> 00:08:14,960
But I'm in control. You are nothing.

135
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:17,820
Let me give you an analogy. What you did was...

136
00:08:17,820 --> 00:08:19,830
parking your car in my spot in the most awful way.

137
00:08:20,389 --> 00:08:22,200
That's why I'm feeling awful.

138
00:08:24,430 --> 00:08:25,899
Get your car out.

139
00:08:27,529 --> 00:08:28,739
I bet you didn't know this,

140
00:08:28,940 --> 00:08:31,440
but I'm in control of your doom.

141
00:08:32,340 --> 00:08:35,279
Since you tried to override me, let me do the same for you.

142
00:08:41,820 --> 00:08:44,279
You will not face your doom which you deserve.

143
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:58,169
Don't worry. When the time is right, you'll get it back.

144
00:08:59,070 --> 00:09:01,070
You'll probably wait for the day of your doom...

145
00:09:01,899 --> 00:09:04,810
because you'll find out that there are worse things than death.

146
00:09:07,869 --> 00:09:08,940
That's called life.

147
00:09:12,050 --> 00:09:13,080
We're from the police.

148
00:09:35,869 --> 00:09:36,999
How beautiful.

149
00:09:43,940 --> 00:09:44,980
You're here.

150
00:09:44,980 --> 00:09:46,610
Don't sound so laid-back.

151
00:09:49,649 --> 00:09:51,149
You should have at least changed your gown.

152
00:09:51,149 --> 00:09:52,690
I didn't, so you could see this.

153
00:09:59,629 --> 00:10:02,700
How can a deity do whatever she wants with the world?

154
00:10:02,899 --> 00:10:04,529
Are you bored at the hospital now?

155
00:10:04,529 --> 00:10:06,869
Try to be a patient here. It's never boring.

156
00:10:07,470 --> 00:10:09,139
Stop throwing yourself a pity party.

157
00:10:09,139 --> 00:10:11,340
I'm like a gardener.

158
00:10:12,539 --> 00:10:15,739
I plant them, water them, and wait with all my heart.

159
00:10:18,009 --> 00:10:19,210
That's all I do.

160
00:10:20,379 --> 00:10:21,879
So you're not responsible for this?

161
00:10:22,350 --> 00:10:24,350
Some don't even get to sprout.

162
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:26,590
And some bloom late.

163
00:10:26,590 --> 00:10:28,560
Some wilt away quickly.

164
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:32,029
Some turn out to be medicinal, and some, poisonous.

165
00:10:33,430 --> 00:10:35,860
And some plants will kill everything around them.

166
00:10:36,930 --> 00:10:38,169
Is that my fault?

167
00:10:38,769 --> 00:10:40,600
Pull them out. Plant only the good ones.

168
00:10:40,970 --> 00:10:42,800
And cherish some plants more than the others.

169
00:10:43,139 --> 00:10:45,039
A garden doesn't belong to a gardener.

170
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:49,779
Then what about me?

171
00:10:50,379 --> 00:10:52,580
What is my position in your garden?

172
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:56,850
You are a butterfly.

173
00:10:57,580 --> 00:10:58,820
For the flowers in my garden.

174
00:10:58,820 --> 00:11:00,190
Until when?

175
00:11:00,989 --> 00:11:02,060
Forever.

176
00:11:05,659 --> 00:11:09,029
You are way too cruel. Especially to a birthday boy.

177
00:11:09,930 --> 00:11:11,600
Birthday? You think you're human?

178
00:11:12,529 --> 00:11:16,440
Have you ever been born? Or human for that matter?

179
00:11:24,239 --> 00:11:25,310
Go.

180
00:11:26,379 --> 00:11:28,180
Go and become someone's wish.

181
00:11:29,220 --> 00:11:31,619
Today is the only day that's possible.

182
00:11:33,690 --> 00:11:35,860
Even my birthday isn't for me.

183
00:11:36,519 --> 00:11:37,820
For humans.

184
00:11:39,029 --> 00:11:40,230
Darn those flowers.

185
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:47,129
It's about time they wilt away.

186
00:11:55,909 --> 00:11:58,110
A bus will arrive shortly.

187
00:12:36,950 --> 00:12:40,619
(Glioblastoma)

188
00:12:47,129 --> 00:12:48,629
(Boyfriend)

189
00:12:54,869 --> 00:12:57,169
- Hey, sweetie.
- Are you busy?

190
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:00,009
No. I'm...

191
00:13:00,310 --> 00:13:02,210
I'm outside. I was meeting up with a writer.

192
00:13:02,610 --> 00:13:04,480
Really? Then can we meet now?

193
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:05,580
Now?

194
00:13:06,110 --> 00:13:07,810
I need to see you right now.

195
00:13:08,749 --> 00:13:09,950
What's wrong?

196
00:13:09,950 --> 00:13:11,649
Let's talk in person.

197
00:13:11,649 --> 00:13:13,450
Come to that cafe. Okay?

198
00:13:14,249 --> 00:13:15,289
Hey...

199
00:13:17,090 --> 00:13:18,159
Gosh.

200
00:13:19,690 --> 00:13:21,759
- She splashed water on that girl.
- No way.

201
00:13:22,659 --> 00:13:25,930
As you can see, this is all I can do because I'm pregnant.

202
00:13:33,369 --> 00:13:34,869
Can you explain...

203
00:13:35,909 --> 00:13:36,980
this?

204
00:13:36,980 --> 00:13:38,450
You're the one who needs to explain things to me.

205
00:13:38,649 --> 00:13:40,110
You're the mistress.

206
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:41,649
You expect me, his wife, to explain what happened?

207
00:13:41,649 --> 00:13:43,220
Where did you learn your manners?

208
00:13:46,989 --> 00:13:50,090
I see. That's what happened.

209
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:54,360
Fine.

210
00:13:55,529 --> 00:13:57,060
That explains everything.

211
00:13:58,100 --> 00:14:00,129
I heard that you met here for the first time.

212
00:14:00,129 --> 00:14:02,800
Did you look through his phone?

213
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:03,800
You don't think I didn't?

214
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:06,039
Then you must have seen how he never called me on weekends...

215
00:14:06,039 --> 00:14:08,409
and answered my calls at night.

216
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:10,940
Whenever I couldn't reach him, he told me his phone died,

217
00:14:10,940 --> 00:14:13,009
it was on silent mode, and he was working.

218
00:14:13,009 --> 00:14:14,649
You must've read those texts then.

219
00:14:15,080 --> 00:14:17,279
That always bothered me.

220
00:14:19,149 --> 00:14:20,789
I knew something was off, but...

221
00:14:21,860 --> 00:14:23,159
Now, this explains everything.

222
00:14:23,159 --> 00:14:25,759
Are you telling me you didn't know he was married?

223
00:14:25,759 --> 00:14:27,889
Yes. I didn't.

224
00:14:27,889 --> 00:14:29,800
You didn't know after dating him for three months?

225
00:14:30,430 --> 00:14:31,529
Stop lying to me!

226
00:14:31,529 --> 00:14:34,269
You didn't know your husband was cheating on you for three months.

227
00:14:34,269 --> 00:14:35,369
Hey!

228
00:14:38,970 --> 00:14:40,769
So you're saying you didn't do anything wrong?

229
00:14:41,310 --> 00:14:42,480
Is that it?

230
00:14:43,739 --> 00:14:44,739
I guess so.

231
00:14:44,739 --> 00:14:47,050
"I guess so"? You're unbelievable.

232
00:14:47,050 --> 00:14:48,720
Then whom should I splash water on?

233
00:14:59,730 --> 00:15:01,800
You can at least take it out on me.

234
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:04,600
But I can't even take it out on you.

235
00:15:05,169 --> 00:15:07,700
It's all that jerk's fault. What should I do?

236
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:09,940
Why are you telling me your sob story?

237
00:15:11,470 --> 00:15:12,470
Right.

238
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:14,869
I shouldn't say that to you.

239
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:23,249
So...

240
00:15:25,050 --> 00:15:27,050
you can keep blaming me.

241
00:15:27,619 --> 00:15:28,690
What?

242
00:15:28,690 --> 00:15:30,090
Pretend that your gentle, innocent husband...

243
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:33,889
was deceived by an awful woman and almost ruined his life.

244
00:15:34,730 --> 00:15:36,460
Be it 10 or 50 years.

245
00:15:36,899 --> 00:15:39,100
Live happily with that cheater for a long time.

246
00:15:41,970 --> 00:15:45,139
That will be better for your child too.

247
00:15:54,180 --> 00:15:55,350
- Are you okay?
- Gosh.

248
00:15:55,619 --> 00:15:57,649
- Oh, no.
- I'm not okay.

249
00:15:57,980 --> 00:16:00,389
- Should you go to a hospital?
- Are you okay?

250
00:16:03,060 --> 00:16:05,090
Taxi! Right here!

251
00:16:05,529 --> 00:16:06,759
Right here. Yes.

252
00:16:06,759 --> 00:16:09,529
Wait. Be careful.

253
00:16:10,930 --> 00:16:12,700
Be careful.

254
00:16:13,899 --> 00:16:16,340
Sir, drive us to a nearby hospital with OBGYNs.

255
00:16:31,889 --> 00:16:33,520
The mother is okay.

256
00:16:33,889 --> 00:16:36,290
This happens frequently when mothers are stressed.

257
00:16:36,760 --> 00:16:38,929
- You don't have to worry.
- Okay.

258
00:16:38,929 --> 00:16:40,090
Are you her guardian?

259
00:16:41,429 --> 00:16:42,429
No.

260
00:16:43,260 --> 00:16:47,869
She's just a mutual friend. Something like that.

261
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:51,240
Do you know her guardian's number?

262
00:16:53,209 --> 00:16:54,209
Yes.

263
00:16:58,179 --> 00:17:01,010
(Boyfriend)

264
00:17:01,409 --> 00:17:04,520
Then can you fill this out for me?

265
00:17:09,619 --> 00:17:12,530
(Jo Dae Han)

266
00:17:12,530 --> 00:17:14,189
(Phone number)

267
00:17:16,959 --> 00:17:19,399
(Relationship to the patient)

268
00:17:23,439 --> 00:17:26,310
(Relationship to the patient)

269
00:17:26,310 --> 00:17:29,780
