00:42:26,370 --> 00:42:27,640
Who are you?

542
00:42:32,410 --> 00:42:33,780
What do you want?

543
00:42:41,890 --> 00:42:43,320
Is it cake?

544
00:42:45,220 --> 00:42:47,590
We don't have time. You're going to die soon.

545
00:43:00,840 --> 00:43:02,269
Exactly 100 days later.

546
00:43:08,849 --> 00:43:12,249
What... By any chance,

547
00:43:13,019 --> 00:43:15,149
are you from the hospital?

548
00:43:16,419 --> 00:43:17,820
Do you think a doctor can do that?

549
00:43:17,820 --> 00:43:20,629
No, I'm sure they can't.

550
00:43:21,160 --> 00:43:23,160
My birthday doesn't come easily.

551
00:43:23,499 --> 00:43:26,530
It travels worldwide and through the fates of many people.

552
00:43:27,070 --> 00:43:29,099
So hurry up and make a wish before it's too late.

553
00:43:33,300 --> 00:43:35,809
I didn't know glioblastoma would bring this kind of symptom.

554
00:43:39,039 --> 00:43:40,879
- What?
- I'm hallucinating.

555
00:43:41,079 --> 00:43:42,479
This is so cool.

556
00:43:45,519 --> 00:43:47,320
I guess you need more time.

557
00:43:47,849 --> 00:43:50,890
This situation is very unrealistic, so I understand.

558
00:43:50,890 --> 00:43:51,959
What?

559
00:43:53,629 --> 00:43:56,360
It's okay. My birthday isn't over yet.

560
00:44:05,300 --> 00:44:06,470
See you later.

561
00:44:25,660 --> 00:44:26,890
Is this a dream?

562
00:44:28,360 --> 00:44:29,530
Of course not.

563
00:44:52,379 --> 00:44:55,689
No, wait. My gosh.

564
00:44:56,490 --> 00:44:59,490
I don't get it. I really don't.

565
00:45:25,419 --> 00:45:26,649
It's taking longer than expected.

566
00:45:41,769 --> 00:45:44,439
What's going on? Where am I?

567
00:45:49,840 --> 00:45:50,979
My house.

568
00:45:52,709 --> 00:45:54,709
Sit down. Make yourself at home.

569
00:45:54,979 --> 00:45:56,079
It's his house?

570
00:45:56,910 --> 00:45:58,579
Did I get kidnapped?

571
00:45:58,579 --> 00:46:01,450
I guess you could say that. But to be more exact,

572
00:46:01,649 --> 00:46:03,990
I came into your dream without permission.

573
00:46:05,360 --> 00:46:06,390
My dream?

574
00:46:14,800 --> 00:46:17,039
So you're saying this is a dream?

575
00:46:26,510 --> 00:46:27,579
Seriously?

576
00:46:31,649 --> 00:46:33,519
- Is this real?
- I know you're dreaming,

577
00:46:33,519 --> 00:46:35,649
but have some manners. This is my house.

578
00:46:36,289 --> 00:46:37,820
Look who's talking. You also...

579
00:46:38,559 --> 00:46:42,090
By the way, why do you keep talking to me without honorifics?

580
00:46:42,629 --> 00:46:44,099
You talked to me like that first.

581
00:46:44,930 --> 00:46:47,200
- I did?
- "Just bring doom to this world."

582
00:46:47,200 --> 00:46:48,800
You said it without honorifics, so I thought that's what you wanted.

583
00:46:48,800 --> 00:46:51,499
I wasn't talking to you when I said that.

584
00:46:53,539 --> 00:46:55,039
Then whom were you talking to?

585
00:46:57,010 --> 00:46:58,439
I'm doom itself.

586
00:47:04,820 --> 00:47:07,450
So you're telling me this is a dream?

587
00:47:14,890 --> 00:47:15,930
What?

588
00:47:18,099 --> 00:47:19,829
Where's the front door?

589
00:47:20,160 --> 00:47:21,399
I'm going to go home.

590
00:47:33,849 --> 00:47:36,079
I guess you don't like the location.

591
00:47:47,530 --> 00:47:48,689
It's where you wanted to go.

592
00:47:53,700 --> 00:47:54,800
It's for the cake.

593
00:47:57,470 --> 00:47:58,599
So are you saying...

594
00:47:59,570 --> 00:48:01,370
you're doom?

595
00:48:02,039 --> 00:48:04,640
I'm responsible for everything that dies or gets destroyed.

596
00:48:05,579 --> 00:48:08,410
Then why not end the world yourself? Why do you keep asking me for help?

597
00:48:08,410 --> 00:48:09,749
Do you think I haven't tried?

598
00:48:10,950 --> 00:48:12,079
It didn't work.

599
00:48:12,379 --> 00:48:14,189
It's probably because I'm just a small part of a system.

600
00:48:14,189 --> 00:48:15,749
What? I don't get what you mean.

601
00:48:15,749 --> 00:48:19,019
In other words, you guys have more authority than I do.

602
00:48:20,090 --> 00:48:21,959
It's how mother nature works.

603
00:48:22,459 --> 00:48:24,860
But this time, I'm hoping it might be different...

604
00:48:25,459 --> 00:48:26,829
because it's what a human being wants.

605
00:48:27,669 --> 00:48:29,970
But why does that have to be me?

606
00:48:29,970 --> 00:48:32,039
No one's ever looked up to a shooting star...

607
00:48:32,039 --> 00:48:33,300
and made a wish like you.

608
00:48:36,370 --> 00:48:40,550
Then do you disappear if you don't grant a wish?

609
00:48:40,550 --> 00:48:42,410
That's what happens in fantasy novels.

610
00:48:45,180 --> 00:48:46,220
Of course not.

611
00:48:46,519 --> 00:48:47,849
It's just a small event.

612
00:48:48,019 --> 00:48:51,959
I was told to become someone's wish on the day I was born.

613
00:48:57,129 --> 00:48:59,329
Is this a nightmare?

614
00:49:01,599 --> 00:49:03,129
Your life is a nightmare.

615
00:49:03,970 --> 00:49:05,039
What?

616
00:49:10,640 --> 00:49:12,539
Unfortunately, it's time for you to wake up.

617
00:49:13,809 --> 00:49:14,879
What?

618
00:49:32,300 --> 00:49:33,700
It was a dream.

619
00:49:35,729 --> 00:49:36,899
It was a dream.

620
00:49:55,689 --> 00:49:58,419
It was a dream. I swear it was.

621
00:50:03,329 --> 00:50:06,030
Look at all this dirt.

622
00:50:06,729 --> 00:50:09,499
My gosh, that crazy punk!

623
00:50:09,499 --> 00:50:12,169
Is he American or what?

624
00:50:14,070 --> 00:50:15,539
My gosh.

625
00:50:39,729 --> 00:50:40,999
I'll help you feel no pain.

626
00:50:46,240 --> 00:50:48,510
You won't feel any kind of pain as you die.

627
00:50:48,570 --> 00:50:49,570
What do you say?

628
00:51:00,590 --> 00:51:02,919
I'd like a roll of gimbap.

629
00:51:04,220 --> 00:51:05,320
Fine.

630
00:51:09,530 --> 00:51:11,399
I'll grant you another wish.

631
00:51:12,760 --> 00:51:14,629
Not something you wished for when you were drunk...

632
00:51:14,629 --> 00:51:16,470
but something you truly want.

633
00:51:18,570 --> 00:51:20,039
But this is as far as I can go.

634
00:51:22,740 --> 00:51:27,379
(Original Gimbap)

635
00:51:31,950 --> 00:51:34,289
Let's not listen to the lunatic.

636
00:51:35,149 --> 00:51:36,519
Don't listen to him.

637
00:51:43,559 --> 00:51:47,030
My gosh, does everyone in the city go to work using the subway?

638
00:51:47,030 --> 00:51:48,899
Why can't they all just disappear?

639
00:52:18,660 --> 00:52:21,030
See? You also want it.

640
00:52:23,570 --> 00:52:24,640
You...

641
00:52:44,320 --> 00:52:48,059
I'm sick. I'm definitely sick.

642
00:52:53,629 --> 00:52:54,729
Ms. Tak.

643
00:52:58,999 --> 00:53:01,070
Thanks to the cafe owner downstairs,

644
00:53:01,070 --> 00:53:03,579
I postponed my resignation to tomorrow again.

645
00:53:04,840 --> 00:53:07,479
Ms. Jo, about yesterday...

646
00:53:07,479 --> 00:53:09,280
Mr. Park isn't coming to work today.

647
00:53:09,479 --> 00:53:11,749
He probably went to kneel before his girlfriend again.

648
00:53:11,849 --> 00:53:14,249
- What?
- He was too hysterical yesterday.

649
00:53:14,249 --> 00:53:16,450
So we assumed he fought with his girlfriend again.

650
00:53:16,450 --> 00:53:18,519
Da In heard them fight on the rooftop.

651
00:53:19,220 --> 00:53:20,860
Apparently, it was a huge mess.

652
00:53:21,760 --> 00:53:24,800
He really needs to stop bringing in his private life to work.

653
00:53:26,129 --> 00:53:27,370
Thank you for this.

654
00:53:29,229 --> 00:53:31,700
Sure. Enjoy your coffee.

655
00:53:31,700 --> 00:53:35,070
Just don't get furious and end up quitting your job.

656
00:53:35,439 --> 00:53:38,039
If you quit, we'll have to suffer. You know that, right?

657
00:53:40,110 --> 00:53:41,849
Why aren't you answering me?

658
00:53:41,849 --> 00:53:42,910
Hey.

659
00:53:45,379 --> 00:53:46,519
Ms. Tak.

660
00:53:47,090 --> 00:53:49,450
The writer for "Siberia" is in the meeting room.

661
00:53:49,450 --> 00:53:50,620
Already?

662
00:53:52,959 --> 00:53:54,559
It's not time for the meeting yet.

663
00:53:54,559 --> 00:53:57,800
Writers can be really self-centered.

664
00:54:08,939 --> 00:54:10,840
Where's the writer?

665
00:54:11,209 --> 00:54:12,640
He's inside.

666
00:54:16,809 --> 00:54:17,979
There he is.

667
00:54:26,559 --> 00:54:29,360
Are you a stalker or an American? Just choose one already.

668
00:54:29,430 --> 00:54:30,930
I also sold gimbap and was also a doctor.

669
00:54:30,930 --> 00:54:33,769
What did you do to them? It's like they're bewitched.

670
00:54:33,769 --> 00:54:36,200
I really did bewitch them.

671
00:54:39,599 --> 00:54:43,269
This is driving me crazy. Have I really lost it?

672
00:54:46,079 --> 00:54:47,410
No, you haven't lost it.

673
00:54:48,550 --> 00:54:51,849
The writer is wandering around somewhere. I needed time with you.

674
00:54:52,450 --> 00:54:53,579
How do you know?

675
00:54:53,579 --> 00:54:54,820
I know because I sent him somewhere.

676
00:54:54,820 --> 00:54:57,059
No, not that. How can you read my mind?

677
00:54:58,919 --> 00:55:00,689
I guess you're a little dull.

678
00:55:01,360 --> 00:55:02,430
By any chance, are you...

679
00:55:02,530 --> 00:55:04,399
I have a question for you.

680
00:55:05,399 --> 00:55:08,200
Why do you work here if you hate the CEO and the firm?

681
00:55:10,340 --> 00:55:12,269
Should I get rid of your CEO for you?

682
00:55:13,240 --> 00:55:15,010
I can make it happen if that's your wish.

683
00:55:15,309 --> 00:55:16,870
Stop reading my mind.

684
00:55:16,970 --> 00:55:19,709
To be more exact, I hear things. I don't read them.

685
00:55:19,709 --> 00:55:20,979
Stop listening.

686
00:55:22,079 --> 00:55:23,720
Then accept my offer.

687
00:55:23,720 --> 00:55:27,050
I'm unable to read or hear the minds of those who make a promise with me.

688
00:55:29,849 --> 00:55:30,890
Get out.

689
00:55:35,530 --> 00:55:37,200
I'll just leave instead.

690
00:55:41,999 --> 00:55:45,240
I'm going to go and meet Ms. Lee Hyun.

691
00:55:48,439 --> 00:55:50,039
Thank you for the coffee.

692
00:55:57,180 --> 00:55:58,979
Ji Na.

693
00:55:58,979 --> 00:56:01,220
Hey, I just woke up.

694
00:56:01,220 --> 00:56:02,720
Why are you calling? Aren't you going to come anyway?

695
00:56:02,720 --> 00:56:05,019
Something's driving me nuts.

696
00:56:05,419 --> 00:56:07,689
What happened? Did your CEO bother you again?

697
00:56:08,490 --> 00:56:10,999
A doctor... No, this American...

698
00:56:10,999 --> 00:56:13,700
No, this crazy guy... I mean, this guy who sells gimbap...

699
00:56:15,669 --> 00:56:18,599
- Gosh, where do I begin?
- What?

700
00:56:23,039 --> 00:56:26,079
("Welcoming the Destruction of Lowell")

701
00:56:47,300 --> 00:56:50,939
Never mind. I'll tell you when we meet.

702
00:57:06,220 --> 00:57:10,689
Nothing changed even after I was told that I'll be dying.

703
00:57:12,490 --> 00:57:15,959
You're not scared of things you can't see...

704
00:57:16,559 --> 00:57:19,660
such as death or destruction.

705
00:57:20,229 --> 00:57:22,200
But once they become visible,

706
00:57:22,829 --> 00:57:26,200
your fear suddenly becomes real.

707
00:57:46,289 --> 00:57:47,530
Pain...

708
00:57:48,390 --> 00:57:49,689
is real.

709
00:58:00,200 --> 00:58:01,769
Oh, dear.

710
00:58:11,149 --> 00:58:14,890
Tell me. Who's having fun playing around with my life?

711
00:58:15,789 --> 00:58:16,849
Hey!

712
01:00:02,160 --> 01:00:03,860
The deity is on my side.

713
01:00:04,700 --> 01:00:07,669
Choose. Will you die here and now?

714
01:00:09,570 --> 01:00:11,240
Or will you take my hand?

715
01:00:23,809 --> 01:00:25,019
And the answer is...

716
01:00:26,320 --> 01:00:27,490
Me.

717
01:01:00,149 --> 01:01:04,919
And just like that, I held Myul Mang's hand.

718
01:01:43,459 --> 01:01:46,030
(Doom at Your Service)

719
01:01:46,559 --> 01:01:48,430
You said to become a human's wish.

720
01:01:48,930 --> 01:01:52,070
But that human's wish happens to be doom.

721
01:01:52,999 --> 01:01:57,209
Why me? Why? Why must it be me?

722
01:01:57,479 --> 01:01:58,579
Fate.

723
01:01:59,180 --> 01:02:00,180
Smile.

724
01:02:00,180 --> 01:02:02,379
Why are you so nice to me all of a sudden?

725
01:02:02,510 --> 01:02:03,780
Get off me!

726
01:02:03,780 --> 01:02:06,120
I'll take care of it. You should go inside and eat.

727
01:02:06,149 --> 01:02:08,320
Shall we meet again tomorrow? Should I go pick you up?

728
01:02:08,419 --> 01:02:09,419
What's with you?

729
01:02:09,419 --> 01:02:11,360
You should be a bit more clingy.

730
01:02:11,590 --> 01:02:12,860
What? To you?

731
01:02:13,189 --> 01:02:15,030
No, to your fate that came to you.

732
01:02:19,023 --> 01:02:21,123
<i>Dramaday.net</i>
